gomodel:SYNGO_2398  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Results section: \"Synaptic Vesicles Are Capable of Accumulating Glu via Activation\nof Endogenous GAPDH/3-PGK\"\n\n- Literal: \"Synaptic vesicles were incubated for various periods\nwith [3H]Glu in the presence or absence of 2 mM GAP, NAD,\nand Pi and 0.1 mM ADP. Vesicular Glu uptake was dependent\non the presence of the GAPDH/3-PGK substrate mixture\nthroughout the incubation period(s) tested and was approximately\nlinear up to 6 min under these conditions (Fig. 3A). When\nany one of the components was omitted from the incubation\nmixture, vesicular Glu uptake was not supported (Fig. 3B).\". Experimental description: Methods:\n\n- Literal: \"Preparation of Subcellular Fractions-Synaptic vesicles were pre- pared from bovine cerebrum through the discontinuous sucrose gradi- ent procedure as described previously\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6893-6177" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5265-6306" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-01" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2398" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9913" .

